The paper focuses on detecting and identifying UAVs using machine learning techniques applied to encrypted Wi-Fi traffic. This falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) as it deals with potential risks to public security and personal privacy. The use of machine learning algorithms for detection and identification suggests that the paper may also fall under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The fact that the proposed framework extracts features from packet size and inter-arrival time of Wi-Fi traffic suggests that it may also fall under the category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also mentions video streaming, which suggests that it may fall under the category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV) or multimedia (cs.MM).
